defaultI have 
defaultan MA from 
defaultOxford University and am a barrister. I’ve
default been an independent business consultant for several years, specialising most recently in project risk, and was founder chair (now non-executive director) of the medical online research company, Medix UK. In 1996, 
defaultI was Chief Executive of the Central Computing and Telecommunications Agency reporting to the Cabinet Office. This note is written in my private capacity; it is not intended to represent the views of Medix.
default&#xa0;
default  As a result of experience acquired at Medix, I
default am familiar with the practical difficulties involved in designing, conducting and analysing surveys of professionals’ opinion
defaults
default in such a way as to be confident that the results of such surveys are an accurate reflection of 
defaultthose
default opinion
defaults
default. Drawing on that 
defaultexperience, this evidence will address the following question: 
default“
defaultTo what extent does AR5 reflect the range of views among climate scientists?”
